<TITLE> 170 postal staffers laid off </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 25 (bdnews24.com) -- The Chittagong zone post office has recently laid off some 170 third- and fourth-class employees. The workers worked on the muster roll for the last five years. "We received a letter from the director general's office Saturday. The letter relieved 170 men of service," said Foyzul Azim, assistant postmaster general for Chittagong zone. bdnews24.
